Smelvin <Da Bashin' Iggles> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulodragan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>lodragan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/25/01 4:16:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=421.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best Possible 4 person PK/Leveling team on Sullon.</span><hr size=1> I would have to disagree with your accessment of mages.<br>
<br>
I ran with a group of 6 mages.  We used a mixture of pets and would demolish just about any red spawn.<br>
<br>
In PvP we took out normal mixed groups with ease - and always ran off twinks even with thier MR - with 6 mages and 6 pets all casting at once - something is bound to land.  At higher levels you get MR lowering debuffs (Malaisment line), pet dual wield, focus items, mod rods etc.<br>
 <br>
You can also multiply the number of tanks by how many pets you can chain cast, i.e. if a mage can chain cast 3 pets before running out of mana - that is potentially 3 X 6 = 18 pets you would have to deal with if timed right by the mages.<br>
<br>
The only other combo that I might see as viable would be to replace a mage with a Druid (mobility healing buffs) or an Enchanter (clarity debuffs buffs mez) and a second mage with a Shaman (debuffs  poison/ailement resistance buffs/debuffs good damage output healing), so you end up with:<br>
<br>
Mobility group:<br>
Druid<br>
Shaman<br>
Mage<br>
Mage<br>
Mage<br>
Mage<br>
<br>
or <br>
<br>
PvP powerhouse group:<br>
Enchanter<br>
Shaman<br>
Mage<br>
Mage<br>
Mage <br>
Mage<br>
<br>
For the purposes of the original poster - drop off 2 mages and you get a mini powerhouse group. <p>-lodragan <br>
High Elf Magician [Sect] Sullon Zek<br>
