</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvenomss.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Venomss</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/6/01 9:22:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=421.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best Possible 4 person PK/Leveling team on Sullon.</span><hr size=1> I have played evils most all the time in Tallon/Vallon zek play, so I will engineer your team on those classes most annoying to me (still suiting neutral and good needs).<br>
<br>
They key to my contribution is Speed, Surprise, and High Damage. SHAMAN, DRUID, MONK, BARD.<br>
<br>
Shaman-sow, slows, heals, dots, non-magicbased dd, and a pet to chase and interupt, DOTS. RESIST BUFFS.<br>
<br>
Druid-SNARE, more sow, more heals, more non magic dd, more DOTS, TRACKING, and Ports-great since you guys will play together, you can show up and start wailing or disappear when fights turn poor.( wizard if evil) <br>
<br>
Monk-with the backing of a shaman, very fierce...will be able to tank for many lvls.  (I see many monk/shaman combos up into the 40s).  Train and Feign, fast-fast hits for interupts, very good choice for dungeon pvp. Also able to capitalize off druid Damage shields.<br>
<br>
Bard-snare, FEAR(now this lightskinned crew can fearkite), CHARM(vs pets or mobs), speed, dots, mana-increased recovery (to recover from taking the chanters spot) crowd control.(shadowknight if evil)<br>
<br>
 This crew can invis, recon their targets, drop in, keep your healers interupted, dot your tanks, take away your pets, TRACK you down, and makes up for beign light skinned in PvE by having the option of fearkiting, and shaman slows.  <br>
<br>
They are admittedly light skinned, with no true plate wearing tank, but the idea is to do hellacious damage immediately, creating a loss of opponents numbers immediately.  Think Stormtrooper tactics (think Germans, not the idiots in white armor paid to shoot stuff and die from Luke Skywalker)<br>
If things get hairy, they can back up and let their mobility create distance, thereby letting dots do their work.  <br>
<br>
I think this could be a very good combo for the neutrals (and goodies if they are paying attention) Let me know what you think of the theory, and justifications.<br>
<br>
-Venoms <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elegance>Elegance</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/6/01 8:03:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=421.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best Possible 4 person PK/Leveling team on Sullon.</span><hr size=1> the mages go down to anyone who attacks them, one rogue and one monk could take out 2 of the 4 mages before they even had a clue what was going on, and Im talking pure melee, yeah you would have the ability to deal some nasty damage, and an unlimited supply of bandaids, but really how much ass are you gonna suck when your group goes oom?  <p>Disclaimer: for the love of God don't Actually shoot any living creature...<br>If you do, at least make sure you clear your internet history so I dont get blamed</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showMessageRange?topicID=421.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showMessage?topicID=440.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showMessage?topicID=436.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=421.topic&index=25><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.emailToFriend?topicID=421.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="